    "sub_topic": "Interpolation and extrapolation of data using Lagrange polynomials",
    "message_1": "Consider the following data set:\n\n|x      | y     |\n|-------|-------|\n| 0     | 1     |\n| 1     | -2    |\n| 2     | 5     |\n| 4     | 7     |\n| 5     | 6     |\n\nUsing the Lagrange interpolation polynomial, find the approximate value of y when x=3.",
    "message_2": "To find the approximate value of y when x=3 using the Lagrange interpolation polynomial, we will use the formula:\n\nL(x) = y0 * l0(x) + y1 * l1(x) + y2 * l2(x) + y3 * l3(x) + y4 * l4(x)\n\nwhere L(x) is the interpolated value at x, and li(x) are the Lagrange basis polynomials defined as:\n\nli(x) = Π((x - xj) / (xi - xj)) for j = 0, 1, ..., n and j ≠ i\n\nFor our data set, we have:\n\nx0 = 0, y0 = 1\nx1 = 1, y1 = -2\nx2 = 2, y2 = 5\nx3 = 4, y3 = 7\nx4 = 5, y4 = 6\n\nNow, we will calculate the Lagrange basis polynomials for x=3:\n\nl0(3) = ((3-1)*(3-2)*(3-4)*(3-5))/((0-1)*(0-2)*(0-4)*(0-5)) = (-2*-1*-1*-2)/(1*2*4*5) = 4/40 = 1/10\nl1(3) = ((3-0)*(3-2)*(3-4)*(3-5))/((1-0)*(1-2)*(1-4)*(1-5)) = (3*1*1*2)/(1*-1*-3*-4) = 6/12 = 1/2\nl2(3) = ((3-0)*(3-1)*(3-4)*(3-5))/((2-0)*(2-1)*(2-4)*(2-5)) = (3*2*-1*-2)/(2*1*-2*-3) = 12/12 = 1\nl3(3) = ((3-0)*(3-1)*(3-2)*(3-5))/((4-0)*(4-1)*(4-2)*(4-5)) = (3*2*1*-2)/(4*3*2*-1) = -12/-24 = 1/2\nl4(3) = ((3-0)*(3-1)*(3-2)*(3-4))/((5-0)*(5-1)*(5-2)*(5-4)) = (3*2*1*1)/(5*4*3*1) = 6/60 = 1/10\n\nNow, we can find the approximate value of y when x=3 using the Lagrange interpolation polynomial:\n\nL(3) = y0 * l0(3) + y1 * l1(3) + y2 * l2(3) + y3 * l3(3) + y4 * l4(3)\nL(3) = 1 * (1/10) + (-2) * (1/2) + 5 * 1 + 7 * (1/2) + 6 * (1/10)\nL(3) = 0.1 - 1 + 5 + 3.5 + 0.6\nL(3) = 8.2\n\nSo, the approximate value of y when x=3 is 8.2."
